description: Denny Tamaki, governor of Okinawa prefecture, says his personal story is deeply entwined with the U.S. military’s presence on the island.
title: Okinawa's governor strives for regional diplomacy as tensions in Asia-Pacific rise

description: An newly discovered asteroid will be captured by Earth's gravity this fall. The "mini-moon" will spend about two months in Earth's orbit, before being flung back on its normal path around the sun.
title: A new 'mini-moon' comes to Earth this fall

description: The Federal Trade Commission said pharmacy benefit managers created a "perverse drug rebate system" that artificially inflated the cost of insulin.
title: FTC sues insulin middlemen, saying they pocket billions while patients face high costs

description: FBI agents boarded a vessel managed by the same company as the cargo ship that caused the collapse of the Francis Scott Key Bridge in March.
title: FBI agents board Baltimore ship linked to Singaporean company sued in bridge collapse

description: The purpose is to raise awareness on the U.K.'s low paternity leave benefits, which currently stand at two weeks of paid time off for new fathers.
title: U.K. dads are wrapping baby slings on male statues to push for more paternity leave

description: Chemicals used in food packaging and linked with health problems have been detected in the human body. The chemicals can move from packaging into food.
title: Hazardous chemicals in food packaging can also be found in people

description: Gen Z and millennial voters make up nearly half of the eligible voting population in this year’s election. In Georgia, the race is on to get them registered before early voting begins this month.
title: As early voting nears in Georgia, all eyes are on whether young voters will turn out

description: President Biden has been receding from the spotlight as the campaign marches on. But he still holds the highest office in the land for another four months and he’s is trying to make the most of it.
title: How Biden is getting used to life as a lame duck president

description: Democrats and Republicans both think they can win the state's Second Congressional District —  one of the swingiest in the country — where immigration and abortion rights are dominating the debate.
title: The contest in one New Mexico swing district mirrors a larger, anxious electorate

description: A beloved heirloom variety of New Mexico red chile commands high prices because of its scarcity. Finding farmers to continue cultivating it has become a challenge.
title: A rare treat getting rarer: Chimayo Red, New Mexico's 'holy chile'

description: Neighbors in Greensboro say Ryan Routh, the man accused of pointing a rifle at the golf course where Donald Trump was playing, wasn't someone they knew well. But he was well-known to law enforcement.
title: In his hometown, Trump's alleged would-be assassin acted like he was 'above the law'
